# iCloud iOS Simulator Workflow

This project lives under an iCloud Drive path. When running iOS simulator previews directly from the workspace, Xcode/Flutter build artifacts can inherit macOS extended attributes such as `com.apple.provenance`, causing simulator codesign failures like:

```text
resource fork, Finder information, or similar detritus not allowed
Failed to codesign .../Flutter.framework/Flutter
```

## Required Preview Flow

- For `flutter run` on iOS simulators, first sync the current project to a non-iCloud temp path, then run from there.
- Preferred temp path: `/tmp/diandian-sim-preview`.
- Exclude generated/heavy folders: `.git`, `build`, `.dart_tool`.

```bash
rm -rf "/tmp/diandian-sim-preview"
rsync -a --exclude='.git' --exclude='build' --exclude='.dart_tool' \
  "<workspace>/" "/tmp/diandian-sim-preview/"
flutter run -d <simulator-device-id>
```

Use the original workspace for edits. The temp copy is only for simulator build/run.
